.TH "host_trace_buffer_show" 9 "host_trace_buffer_show" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
host_trace_buffer_show \- firmware ring buffer (trace only)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" host_trace_buffer_show
.BI "(struct device *cdev "  ","
.BI "struct device_attribute *attr "  ","
.BI "char *buf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cdev" 12
pointer to embedded class device
.IP "attr" 12
?
.IP "buf" 12
the buffer returned
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
A sysfs 'read/write' shost attribute.

You will only be able to read 4k bytes of ring buffer at a time.
In order to read beyond 4k bytes, you will have to write out the
offset to the same attribute, it will move the pointer.
